<heading id="B3088105FF9EFFE2FE0518D786D3B0FE" box="[412,903,730,757]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="808" reason="5">
<taxonomicName id="2FFF4DEAFF9EFFE2FE0518D786D3B0FE" authority="(Morelet, 1851)" baseAuthorityName="Morelet" baseAuthorityYear="1851" box="[412,903,730,757]" class="Gastropoda" family="Planorbidae" genus="Antillorbis" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="9" pageNumber="808" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aeruginosus">
<emphasis id="DA8BEA7BFF9EFFE2FE0518D78790B0FE" bold="true" box="[412,708,730,757]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="808">Antillorbis aeruginosus</emphasis>
(Morelet, 1851)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E8403669FF9EFFE2FF59191D813FB19A" blockId="9.[160,1155,784,913]" pageId="9" pageNumber="808">
We present the first record of this genus and species from St. Thomas. Previous records are from St. Croix, 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF9EFFE2FEF5193E84BBB147" box="[364,495,819,844]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="9" pageNumber="808">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF9EFFE2FE61193E877AB147" box="[504,558,819,844]" name="Haiti" pageId="9" pageNumber="808">Haiti</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF9EFFE2FDA1193E8726B147" box="[568,626,819,844]" name="Cuba" pageId="9" pageNumber="808">Cuba</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="90E876F9FF9EFFE2FD30193E8640B147" box="[681,788,819,844]" name="Dominica" pageId="9" pageNumber="808">Dominica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF9EFFE2FCB9193E8118B147" author="Harry HW &amp; Hubendick B" box="[800,1100,819,844]" pageId="9" pageNumber="808" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref25430" refString="Harry HW, Hubendick B. 1964. The freshwater pulmonate Mollusca of Puerto Rico. K Vet O Vitterh Samh Handl. 9 (5): 1 - 77." type="journal article" year="1964">Harry and Hubendick 1964</bibRefCitation>
). We collected this species from Flamboyan ghut in isolated pools along the drainage. 
<bibRefCitation id="8C6E4B98FF9EFFE2FBDE195884CDB19A" author="Harry HW &amp; Hubendick B" pageId="9" pageNumber="808" pagination="1 - 77" refId="ref25430" refString="Harry HW, Hubendick B. 1964. The freshwater pulmonate Mollusca of Puerto Rico. K Vet O Vitterh Samh Handl. 9 (5): 1 - 77." type="journal article" year="1964">Harry and Hubendick (1964)</bibRefCitation>
discuss the ability of this species to survive prolonged drought.
</paragraph>
